<dl id="n03069c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03069c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03069c"> 69(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tactful &amp; fervent <small>Blue</small> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Transferred to <a name="sh2005f" href="sh2all.htm#sh2005f">Sheet ii-5(f)</a>. Not used in <cite>FW</cite>. </mm> <blockquote class="sources"> Her <mark>tactful and fervent</mark> pleading enabled Frau Wesendonck to persuade her husband, in his generosity, to purchase a small house, roomy and convenient, just on the border of the estate, with a garden attached to it &hellip; It was understood that the artist should pay the rent in music and his personal company. <small> Edouard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESWI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESWI"><cite title="source">Woman: the Inspirer</cite></a>, trans. by Fred Rothwell (1918) 14</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
